WNBA star Brittney Griner has written a book about her struggles as a lesbian at Baylor University and how she was warned by her coach to keep ‘her business’ to herself and warned not to express her sexuality in public.

Baylor University is a rigidly Baptist university in Texas that discourages students from participating in 'advocacy groups which promote understandings of sexuality that are contrary to biblical teaching.'

In her book In My Skin, Griner writes that she was open with Coach Kim Mulkey even before she joined the team.

