Griner was a three-time AP all-American who is the NCAA’s all-time leader in blocked shots, and led the Lady Bears to the 2012 national title.

Last year she was named 'Best Female College Athlete' for her 2012-13 season at Baylor at the ESPY Awards, just weeks after officially coming out as gay - ahead of the WNBA draft.

At the time she said she was still haunted by the memories of her peers refusing to believe she was a girl, questioning her sexual orientation and even groping her physically.

'I was always taller, my feet were always bigger and my voice was deeper,' said Griner, who is 6 feet 8 with a wingspan of 88 inches.

In an honest interview with the Los Angeles Times, the Phoenix Mercury powerhouse described one day in seventh grade when class had just let out and the hallway was flooded with students.

